<TITLE> Bay low deepens into depression </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 16 (dbnews24.com)The well-marked low over the north Bay and the adjoining coast has intensified into a monsoon depression, the weather office said Monday. In a midday bulletin, the Meteorological Department said the depression had been centred about 235km west-southwest of Chittagong port, 215km west of Cox's Bazar and 135km south-southeast of Mongla. "The depression is likely to move northwest and may cross Barisal-Khulna coast by Monday night," the weather office said. "Squally weather may continue to affect the maritime ports and adjoining coastal region." The maritime ports of Chittagong, Cox's Bazar and Mongla have been advised to keep hoisted local cautionary No. 3. Inland river ports have been asked to keep up cautionary signal No. 2. Under the influence of the depression, the low-lying areas of the coastal districts of Chittagong Cox's Bazar, Mongla, Noakhali, Laxmipur, Bhola, Patuakhali, Barisal, Chandpur, Borguna, Pirozpur, Jhalakathi, Bagerhat, Khulna, Satkhira and their offshore inlands and sandbars are likely to experience heavy rain. All fishing boat and trawlers over the north Bay have been advised to remain in shelter until further notice. bdn
